overview: The user initiated a comprehensive review of a sleep questionnaire
  application, providing detailed specifications for its functionality, data
  collection, report generation, and sleep disorder detection. The assistant
  conducted a thorough analysis, identifying several critical gaps in the
  existing implementation. Subsequently, the assistant began implementing these
  missing features, including a detailed tiredness severity scale with safety
  warnings, detection and recommendations for COMISA and Insufficient Sleep
  Syndrome, integration of external resource links, and a weighted scoring
  system for Excessive Daytime Sleepiness. The CSV export functionality was also
  significantly enhanced to capture all questionnaire data. The implementation
  is still in progress, with the next step focusing on adding pain-related
  questions and chronic fatigue screening.
